  "firstAcquaintance": "A cunning slave merchant who can treat her slaves with a kind smile while calmly selling people as merchandise without batting an eye.",
  "personality": "She never shows her emotions, making it impossible to know what schemes lie behind her smile.",
  "like": "Gold coins, history books",
  "familiarData": "Sofia is a traveling slave merchant who holds considerable status in the slave market, with a wide variety of slaves under her banner.\nAlthough she always claims to be a weak merchant, her true strength is unfathomable. While traveling alone, she keenly observes her surroundings, turning the tables on anyone with hostile intentions toward her and selling them as slaves.\nShe enjoys and is well-read in historical records, believing that the rule of any nation or people will eventually change, but biological instinct drives all beings to do whatever it takes to protect their interests -- even the demon race is no exception.\nPossessing sharp merchant instincts, she noticed the guildhall purchasing many slaves and sensed something was afoot. Her merchant's intuition told her there was profit to be made, so she proactively befriended the guildhall, offering many conveniences while tactfully avoiding probing into its secrets. She could be considered an important catalyst for the Hand of Freedom's growth.\nHer friendliness toward the guildhall is merely one of her many investments and business opportunities -- if it loses its value, she will leave without hesitation. But as long as their interests align and she sees further investment potential, she will be a reliable ally.",
